Former Dimension Data CEO Brett Dawson has invested in a number of startups which are focused on fourth industrial revolution technologies. Through his investment incubator platform Campan, Dawson has invested in early-stage startups which he said have the potential to redefine their industries. “Campan is a vehicle through which I can live out my passion for enabling new companies that use technology as an engine to make substantial positive differences in terms of industry and process,” said Dawson. The startups which Campan has invested in include: Dawson said his vision for Campan is to become a leading incubation platform that nurtures emerging businesses to make a difference in society.